To get the project running
---------------------------

Copy the file 'database.yml' and paste it in your 'config' folder
Then edit it, adding your own db username and password

Run...
rvm gemset create portfolio
gem install bundler
bundle install
rake db:create portfolio  //or create the database yourself
rake db:schema:load
rails server


To create your first user and start adding projects
-----------------------------------------------------
Run rake db:seed
Now you can access the app with the following credentials:

email: admin@example.com
pass: password

When you first log in to the application it will prompt you to change these credentials. Please do!



To test S3 from the development environment
-----------------------------------------------

In heroku_env...
enter tour data.
Uncomment ... lines

